                            <comment id="26667" author="pjones" created="Mon, 16 Jan 2012 15:26:54 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;let&apos;s track this under lu-861 and then open a new ticket if the problems still exist with those fixes landed&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="26226" author="laisiyao" created="Tue, 10 Jan 2012 03:24:05 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-861?page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel&amp;amp;focusedCommentId=26225#comment-26225&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-861?page=com.atlassian.jira.plugin.system.issuetabpanels:comment-tabpanel&amp;amp;focusedCommentId=26225#comment-26225&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;According to Jinshan&apos;s comment on &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-861&quot; title=&quot;ASSERTION(!cfs_in_interrupt()) failed on MDS during compilebench over nfsv4&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-861&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-861&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, two fixes may help, this work will be continued after that.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="26163" author="laisiyao" created="Mon, 9 Jan 2012 04:09:03 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;In my local test, I found it&apos;s stack overflow too. I&apos;ll try to decrease stack size a bit and verify it.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="25368" author="laisiyao" created="Tue, 3 Jan 2012 20:26:41 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;nfsd uses splice read/write interface on new kernels, I tested some splice test (from LTP), and it could pass. I&apos;ll do more test later.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="25334" author="green" created="Tue, 3 Jan 2012 07:31:04 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lai, Jinshan, we need to look into this as this potentially underscores how recent clio changes introduced some deadlocks in sendfile path.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23491" author="sarah" created="Tue, 29 Nov 2011 01:48:43 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;debug -1 log&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23460" author="johann" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 08:25:30 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;ah, this is with the default debug mask. Could you please collect one with the debug mask set to -1? Thanks in advance.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23457" author="sarah" created="Mon, 28 Nov 2011 01:05:44 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;debug log of lustre client(NFS server)&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23447" author="sarah" created="Sun, 27 Nov 2011 02:12:55 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;sure, will keep you updated.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23395" author="johann" created="Thu, 24 Nov 2011 11:25:28 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;hm, several nfsd threads seems to be stuck in splice_read (somewhere in cl_page_list_disown() although it is not clear if the stack is reliable).&lt;br/&gt;
Sarah, could you please rerun the test and collect lustre debug logs?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="23092" author="pjones" created="Wed, 16 Nov 2011 09:20:08 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Lai&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Could you please comment on this one?&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Thanks&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Peter&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
